&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Full time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Bedser Hub at Woking hospital are looking to recruit an experienced Advanced Nurse Practitioner to support the delivery of locality hub services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be able to work within a multi-disciplinary team of GPs, Mental Health Practitioners, Social Care Teams, Pharmacists and used to communicating at an advanced level with external partners in Primary and Secondary Care.&lt;br /&gt;You would be working as a Matron within the Hub, be used to working as an autonomous practitioner and making clinical decisions within your scope of practice. Ideally you should be an independant V300 prescriber with advanced assessment skills for managing frailty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with the elderly in roles such as a Nurse Practitioner, Ward Sister or a District Nurse are desirable. &lt;br /&gt;Car driver is essential and the post holder will be required to make home vists and provide cover the Ashford and Thames Medical Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
